{"title_page": "Natasha Smith (diplomat)", "text_new": "{{Underlinked|date=April 2020}}\n\n'''Natasha Smith''' has been the Australian High Commissioner to Canada since February 2018.  The Commission also has responsibility for Bermuda.<ref name=\"otwa\">{{cite web |title=About Us |url=https://canada.embassy.gov.au/otwa/aboutus.html |website=Australian High Commission Canada |publisher=DFAT |accessdate=1 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nHer personal goal as Commissioner is \u201cchampioning diversity issues. This includes working with Canadian counterparts on indigenous issues, gender equality and Lesbian, Gay, Bisexual, Transgender and Intersex (LGBTI) rights.\u201d<ref name=\"CACC\">{{cite web |title=Boardroom Briefings by the Australian High Commissioner to Canada, Her Excellency Natasha Smith |url=https://cacc.com.au/news/boardroom-briefings-by-the-australian-high-commissioner-to-canada-her-excellency-natasha-smith/ |website=Canadian Australian Chamber Of Commerce |accessdate=1 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nSmith earned a Bachelor of Economics from James Cook University and is a Graduate of the Australian Institute of Company Directors.<ref name=\"otwa\" />\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{s-start}}\n{{s-dip}}\n{{s-bef|before=[[Tony Negus]]}}\n{{s-ttl|title=[[List of High Commissioners of Australia to Canada|Australian High Commissioner to Canada]] |years=2018\u2013present}}\n{{s-inc}}\n{{end}}\n\n{{Improve categories|date=March 2020}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Smith, Natasha}}\n[[Category:Australian women diplomats]]\n[[Category:Women ambassadors]]\n[[Category:High Commissioners of Australia to Canada]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n\n\n{{Australia-diplomat-stub}}\n", "text_old": "'''Natasha Smith''' has been the Australian High Commissioner to Canada since February 2018.  The Commission also has responsibility for Bermuda.<ref name=\"otwa\">{{cite web |title=About Us |url=https://canada.embassy.gov.au/otwa/aboutus.html |website=Australian High Commission Canada |publisher=DFAT |accessd